  "chapter": {
    "number": 7,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Israel’s Great Misery"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe is me!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "For I am like one gathering summer fruit",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "at the gleaning of the vineyard;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "there is no cluster to eat,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no early fig that I crave.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The godly man has perished from the earth;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there is no one upright among men.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They all lie in wait for blood;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they hunt one another with a net.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Both hands are skilled at evil;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the prince and the judge demand a bribe.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "When the powerful utters his evil desire,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they all conspire together.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The best of them is like a brier;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the most upright is sharper than a hedge of thorns.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The day for your watchmen has come,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the day of your visitation.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3826
          },
          {
            "text": "Now is the time of their confusion.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not rely on a friend;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not trust in a companion.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Seal the doors of your mouth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from her who lies in your arms.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3827
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For a son dishonors his father,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a daughter rises against her mother,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and a daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "A man’s enemies are the members",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "of his own household.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3828
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Israel’s Confession and Comfort"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But as for me, I will look to the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will wait for the God of my salvation.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "My God will hear me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not gloat over me, my enemy!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Though I have fallen, I will arise;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "though I sit in darkness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD will be my light.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Because I have sinned against Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I must endure the rage of the LORD,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "until He argues my case",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and executes justice for me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He will bring me into the light;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will see His righteousness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then my enemy will see",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and will be covered with shame—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "she who said to me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Where is the LORD your God?”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "My eyes will see her;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "at that time she will be trampled",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "like mud in the streets.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The day for rebuilding your walls will come—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the day for extending your boundary.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "On that day they will come to you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from Assyria and the cities of Egypt,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "even from Egypt to the Euphrates,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3829
          },
          {
            "text": "from sea to sea and mountain to mountain.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then the earth will become desolate",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because of its inhabitants,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "as the fruit of their deeds.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God’s Compassion on Israel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shepherd with Your staff Your people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the flock of Your inheritance.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They live alone in a woodland,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "surrounded by pastures.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3830
          },
          {
            "text": "Let them graze in Bashan and Gilead,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as in the days of old.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As in the days when you came out of Egypt,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will show My wonders.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Nations will see and be ashamed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "deprived of all their might.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will put their hands over their mouths,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their ears will become deaf.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will lick the dust like a snake,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like reptiles slithering on the ground.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will crawl from their holes",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in the presence of the LORD our God;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they will tremble in fear of You.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who is a God like You,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who pardons iniquity",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and passes over the transgression",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "of the remnant of His inheritance—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who does not retain His anger forever,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because He delights in loving devotion?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3831
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He will again have compassion on us;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He will vanquish our iniquities.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You will cast out all our sins",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "into the depths of the sea.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will show faithfulness to Jacob",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and loving devotion to Abraham,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "as You swore to our fathers",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the days of old.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
